Consider a graph $\Gamma$ that is a star with $m>2$ legs
of length $n\geq 2$, so that there are $m$ leaves that are pairwise at
distance $2n$ from one another. Take $\double(\Gamma)$.
This is the $(m,n)$--\emph{spider}.
Optionally, from each foot we can either leave both valence 2 vertices,
and call this a pincer foot, or delete one of them. 
The result is commensurable to a RAAG tree, and has the property that
vertices on different feet have pairwise distance $2n$. 

